{{unreferenced|date=November 2016}} {{subspeciesbox | name = Domestic muscovy duck | image = MuscovyDuck.jpg | image_caption = A Piebald Muscovy drake | status = DOM | genus = Cairina | species = moschata | species_link = Muscovy duck | subspecies = domestica | authority = ([[Robert Arthur Donkin|Donkin]], 1989) | synonyms = ''Cairina moschata momelanotus'' }}
The '''domestic muscovy duck''' (''Cairina moschata domestica'') is a [[domestic duck|domesticated]] form of the wild [[muscovy duck]] originated in [[South America]]. It is bred for [[meat]], [[feathers]], [[poultry egg|eggs]], [[pets]] and sometimes as [[guard dog|guard animals]].<ref>http://www.offthegridnews.com/how-to-2/the-ultimate-homestead-bird/</ref>
==Domestic varieties==
* Black * Blue * Chocolate * Pied (white with any color mixed) * White * Lavender * Bronze * Ripple * and many more pastel colors, but these are very rare.
